{u'poster_path': u'/6b3qdYrvJCMqzdFYTOy5zETjs0d.jpg', u'title': u'Three Times', u'overview': u'There are three stories of women and men: in "A Time for Love" set in 1966, a soldier searches for a young woman he met one afternoon playing pool; "A Time for Freedom," set in a bordello in 1911, revolves around a singer\'s longing to escape her surroundings; in "A Time for Youth" set in 2005 Taipei, a triangle in which a singer has an affair with a photographer while her partner suffers is dramatized. In the first two stories, letters are crucial to the outcome; in the third, it\'s cell-phone calls, text messages, and a computer file. Over the years between the tales, as sexual intimacy becomes more likely and words more free, communication recedes.', u'release_date': u'2005-05-20', u'popularity': 1.173135, u'original_title': u'Zui hao de shi guang', u'backdrop_path': u'/1msxMbbn9nJGPsXbGQpuZXwdLLL.jpg', u'vote_count': 7, u'video': False, u'adult': False, u'vote_average': 6.5, u'genre_ids': [80, 18, 10769, 10749], u'id': 11554, u'original_language': u'zh'}